Gatvol job seekers have held more than 400 contract workers and some of Collins Chabane Municipal officials hostage in Malamulele in Limpopo on Tuesday. One of the Job seekers who declined to be named told Daily Sun that people are angry after the community were told that they will employed in various projects that will take place soon. She said that only few people were hired even though they have been promised that many people will be employed. One of the contractors, Steven Ndhambi said it almost an hour they have locked in the Boxing Gym. Ndhambi said police are trying to free them but they have failed so far. He said many people are on panic since it is hot inside the building.